{"body": "The problem only exists when in production one has a exception notifier that sends an email containing the backtrace + an inspection of the env variables back at the developers. I believe that filling the production machine's memory with a huge inspection string is not one of the admin's favorite things.\r\n\r\nMy solution might be a bit ugly but in development it served me and a couple of my colleagues well when a broken Arel query inspection started filling in more than 2GB of ram.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/2113054", "created_at": "2011-09-16T09:00:48Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2623#issuecomment-2113054", "updated_at": "2011-09-16T09:00:48Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 2623, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/vrinek", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/e1178c7bae28fff8f7c948fb7c8c6c30?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F05a02dfa133a8d4b11d174d2e5d84b78.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/received_events", "gravatar_id": "e1178c7bae28fff8f7c948fb7c8c6c30", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "vrinek", "type": "User", "id": 81346, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/vrinek/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523841e7bd3543c151010a7c"}, "id": 2113054, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2623"}
